'''Liz Edmiston''' (21 May 1945 &ndash; 10 April 2008) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] actress.

She appeared in several TV series [[Sentimental Education]] (1970), [[Now Take My Wife]] (1971) and [[The 14]] (1973), Dickens of London (1976). She also made an appearance on an episode of [[Keeping up Appearances]] (1993) and was married to fellow actor Eric Carte.

She was in poor health with [[diabetes]], from the age of 13 she suffered with type 1 diabetes. 
for much of her life, and died on stage while acting on board the liner [[MV Oriana (1995)]].

