'''Nihilist communism'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ardentpress.com/nihilist-communism/|title=Nihilist Communism {{!}} Ardent Press|website=ardentpress.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Nihilist_Communism.html?id=y0HmZwEACAAJ|title=Nihilist Communism: A Critique of Optimism in the Far Left|last=(Monsieur.)|first=Dupont|date=2009|publisher=Ardent Press|isbn=9781620490396|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://littleblackcart.com/books/communism/nihilist-communism/|title=Books :: Communism :: Nihilist Communism - LBC:: books & ephemera|website=littleblackcart.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2473689.Nihilist_Communism|title=Nihilist Communism|website=Goodreads|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metamute.org/editorial/articles/nihilists-one-less-effort-if-you-would-be-nihilists|title=Nihilists! One Less Effort if You Would be Nihilists {{!}} Mute|website=www.metamute.org|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> is a collection of anti-authoritarian, anti-political, anti-organizational communist perspectives<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/MonsieurDupontNihilistCommunismACritiqueOfOptimismInTheFarLeft|title=Monsieur Dupont Nihilist Communism A Critique Of Optimism In The Far Left|last=Monsieur Dupont}}</ref> cardinally developed by two anglophone authors using the pen names ''Frère''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/category/author/frere-dupont|title=Frére Dupont {{!}} The Anarchist Library|website=theanarchistlibrary.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.metamute.org/editorial/articles/release-to-us-field|title=Release to Us the Field! {{!}} Mute|website=www.metamute.org|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> and ''Le Garçon''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/category/author/le-garcon-dupont|title=Le Garcon Dupont {{!}} The Anarchist Library|website=theanarchistlibrary.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> Since 2003,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/d/Books/Nihilist-Communism-Critique-Optimism-Religious-Ultimate-Triumph/B0019ZRWGK|title=Nihilist Communism: a Critique of Optimism, the Religious Dogma That States There Will Be An Ultimate Triumph of Good Over Evil, in the Far Left|last=Dupont|first=Monsieur|date=2003|publisher=Monsieur Dupont}}</ref> they have written collaboratively as Monsieur Dupont.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1099240.Monsieur_Dupont|title=Monsieur Dupont|website=Goodreads|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://littleblackcart.com/journals/letters-3/|title=Journals :: Letters Journal #3 - LBC:: books & ephemera|website=littleblackcart.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7313833-letters-3|title=Letters #3|website=Goodreads|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref>

Nihilist communism aims to level "a critique of optimism in the far left".<ref name=":0" /> Rather than attempting to establish new and popular sets of positions, it is counterpoised against, among many other things, the "religious" dogma of the Marxist and anarchist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/monsieur-dupont-anarchists-must-say-what-only-anarchists-can-say|title=Anarchists must say what only anarchists can say {{!}} The Anarchist Library|website=theanarchistlibrary.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> milieus. It attempts to disencumber itself of its content in order to explore new concepts and ideas. 

